summary: WANTED CONNECTION    That’s not David Tennant, Grant Gustin, Brenton Thwaites, Matt Smith, UTP it’s Jane Cooper’s Father Vaan...
caption:
WANTED CONNECTION

  That’s not David Tennant, Grant Gustin, Brenton Thwaites, Matt Smith, UTP it’s Jane Cooper’s Father Vaan Nox. He’s UTP years old and a Fairy.

  Vaan fell in love at a early age with a woman called Lara. They lived in the kingdom of Albion, and wed young, having only a single child. Only single, because Lara died during childbirth. However Vaan never let that affect his love for his daughter, instead he tried to love her enough for them both. His daughter, Stella, was always a bit of a trouble maker. As soon as she was walking she was running around. This only became a problem one day when she was running around and didn’t come home for hours. Vaan was worried sick. He had been ready to start a rescue party and trek into dangerous lands when the royal carriage came along. Then there was Stella, holding their queens hand. While everyone bowed. Vaan didn’t bow, instead he ran to his daughter’s side and pulled her into a tight hug. He kissed her forehead and didn’t let go out the small child said Daddy you’re squishing me. Vaan thanked their queen for bringing his child home. Then, Queen Cecilia remarked that her son had technically kidnapped her. Then there was tea. Somehow along the way Queen Cecilia’s visits became something of regularity. By the time Stella was seven, Vaan and the queen were engaged and Vaan became the step-father of the future king, and the husband of the queen. There was never intention of Vaan becoming the ruler of Avalon. In fact the suggestion alone was meant with laughter. He loved Cecilia, and thought there was no other who could be a better ruler. Two years later, right before his daughter’s ninth birthday, he and Cecilia had another child. They struggled with finding the boy a name. In fact they hadn’t even had one by the time Stella’s birthday rolled around. At Stella’s behest Vaan got her a necklace with the number nine on it. It was on her very birthday tragedy struck. The castle was attacked, both Vaan and Cecilia died. Stella entered into the human world, fell to amnesia and became Jane. However, for Vaan, his bright world went dark. One moment he was in the kingdom of Avalon, dying and the next he was in San Francisco about 13 years later. Pulled back from the dead into a strange new world. A/N the name Vaan is totally changeable and you could contact at me at @ofivorywings for more details!
